our notions of Romantic affect. Finally, it answers pivotal questions facing both affect studies and Romanticism about interrelations among language, affect, and materiality. Readers will learn more about the deep history of how poetic language can help us move beyond binary gender and its limiting intellectual and affective ideologies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aRomanticismzGreat Britian. 0aSenses and sensation in literature. 0aSentimentalism in literature. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aLiterature : Literary Criticism. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Gothic & Romance.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847529540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438475295423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438475295/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles